Don't come closer.

772
00:54:06,250 --> 00:54:07,280
Don't come.

773
00:54:07,519 --> 00:54:08,719
I said, don't come closer!

774
00:54:28,469 --> 00:54:29,599
An attorney...

775
00:54:30,840 --> 00:54:32,639
shouldn't beat up her client.

776
00:54:35,039 --> 00:54:36,280
There he is.

777
00:54:36,510 --> 00:54:38,179
- Is he the stalker?
- I guess so.

778
00:54:38,809 --> 00:54:40,679
Please step back.
Move out of the way, please.

779
00:54:40,679 --> 00:54:41,880
He looks completely normal.

780
00:54:41,880 --> 00:54:42,880
Go on.

781
00:54:57,829 --> 00:54:58,869
Hey.

782
00:55:00,869 --> 00:55:02,570
Did everything get sorted out
on the scene?

783
00:55:03,039 --> 00:55:04,239
Yes, almost.

784
00:55:04,440 --> 00:55:06,110
How's Ms. Lee? Is she okay?

785
00:55:06,409 --> 00:55:07,409
She's okay.

786
00:55:07,840 --> 00:55:09,880
She's actually relieved
that things turned out like this.

787
00:55:12,449 --> 00:55:13,480
I'm glad to hear that.

788
00:55:15,679 --> 00:55:16,690
Here.

789
00:55:18,590 --> 00:55:19,590
Thank you.

790
00:55:21,960 --> 00:55:22,960
I...

791
00:55:24,030 --> 00:55:25,389
I never even thought
about the possibility.

792
00:55:26,159 --> 00:55:27,199
Mr. Jun...

793
00:55:28,659 --> 00:55:30,900
I mean, that scum. I can't believe
he's a complete psycho.

794
00:55:32,769 --> 00:55:34,670
I thought he looked normal.

795
00:55:37,610 --> 00:55:39,610
Don't beat yourself up too much.

796
00:55:39,869 --> 00:55:40,909
You see,

797
00:55:41,579 --> 00:55:44,579
those scums usually look
completely normal.

798
00:55:44,780 --> 00:55:46,610
Still,
I can't help beating myself up.

799
00:55:46,610 --> 00:55:49,349
We could prevent a big mishap
thanks to you.

800
00:55:50,989 --> 00:55:52,920
Thanks for saying that.

801
00:55:53,860 --> 00:55:54,960
It's true.

802
00:55:57,659 --> 00:55:58,760
Let's get up.

803
00:55:59,059 --> 00:56:00,230
You need to give a statement
as a witness.

804
00:56:01,059 --> 00:56:02,059
Right.

805
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:06,969
By the way, do you realize that you
keep talking casually to me?

806
00:56:07,070 --> 00:56:08,070
No.

807
00:56:10,409 --> 00:56:12,469
Because you grabbed the bat,

808
00:56:12,469 --> 00:56:14,579
- Ms. Lee...
- I told you I never hit her.

809
00:56:14,579 --> 00:56:16,239
Why would I hit the woman I love?

810
00:56:16,239 --> 00:56:17,679
- You kept banging on her door...
- Gosh.

811
00:56:17,679 --> 00:56:19,579
I'm telling you I never did
such things.

812
00:56:19,880 --> 00:56:22,119
- Why did you pick up the bat...
- Did you see it? Did you?

813
00:56:22,449 --> 00:56:26,219
That's the statement we got. How
dare you raise your voice at me...

814
00:56:26,219 --> 00:56:30,130
Not being loved back by the one
you love is like torture.

815
00:56:30,829 --> 00:56:32,159
But in a way,

816
00:56:32,929 --> 00:56:35,829
being loved by someone
you don't want to be with...

817
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:38,070
and being forced to love
that person back...

818
00:56:38,199 --> 00:56:40,239
could be a bigger torture.

819
00:56:41,969 --> 00:56:43,570
How much of it can be called love?

820
00:56:44,840 --> 00:56:46,510
Where does obsession begin?

821
00:56:50,079 --> 00:56:51,210
And I...

822
00:56:51,980 --> 00:56:54,179
- Why is the office in this area?
- At this moment,

823
00:56:54,280 --> 00:56:55,719
whereabouts am I standing...

824
00:56:55,980 --> 00:56:57,789
between love and obsession?

825
00:56:58,190 --> 00:57:00,119
Physical harm isn't
the only type of abuse.

826
00:57:00,460 --> 00:57:01,760
Stalking is the definition...

827
00:57:01,760 --> 00:57:04,429
of psychological and emotional
stress and abuse.

828
00:57:06,130 --> 00:57:07,659
Unwanted attention...

829
00:57:07,929 --> 00:57:09,000
is also a form of abuse.

830
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:10,829
I would...

831
00:57:11,130 --> 00:57:13,840
like to give myself
a restraining order.

832
00:57:14,340 --> 00:57:16,070
Arrived at the destination.

833
00:57:16,070 --> 00:57:17,769
Ending voice navigation.

834
00:57:18,469 --> 00:57:20,380
This is the address according
to the navigation. Is this it?

835
00:57:20,579 --> 00:57:21,610
Sorry? Oh...

836
00:57:22,679 --> 00:57:24,050
Yes, this is it.

837
00:57:24,449 --> 00:57:25,949
Thank you for the ride.

838
00:57:45,429 --> 00:57:46,900
I just don't want you to worry.

839
00:57:47,440 --> 00:57:51,769
Other than for work-related things
or bumping into you unexpectedly,

840
00:57:51,869 --> 00:57:55,280
I'll stay at least 100m away
from you at all times.

841
00:57:58,309 --> 00:58:00,719
What exactly do you mean by that?

842
00:58:01,079 --> 00:58:02,980
I literally meant what I said.
And...

843
00:58:02,980 --> 00:58:03,989
And?

844
00:58:05,449 --> 00:58:06,889
I'm saying this
in case you got the wrong idea.

845
00:58:07,690 --> 00:58:09,360
I don't like you.

846
00:58:09,690 --> 00:58:13,900
I may have looked like I do because
I feel grateful and indebted to you,

847
00:58:14,130 --> 00:58:15,599
but please don't worry
or get any wrong ideas.

848
00:58:15,599 --> 00:58:17,400
I have no feelings for you
whatsoever.

849
00:58:17,400 --> 00:58:19,130
Really. I'm serious.
Please believe me.

850
00:58:19,329 --> 00:58:20,699
Drive safely.

851
00:58:21,199 --> 00:58:22,199
Hey.

852
00:59:03,340 --> 00:59:05,449
I couldn't even date him.

853
00:59:06,079 --> 00:59:07,980
How many times do I have
these breakup-like situations?

854
00:59:54,800 --> 00:59:57,000
(If you keep looking for me,
I'll find you first.)

855
00:59:57,000 --> 01:00:01,239
"If you keep looking for me,
I'll find you first"?

856
01:00:05,170 --> 01:00:06,840
(Looking for Witness)

857
01:00:08,610 --> 01:00:09,880
(Please call this number.)

858
01:00:13,610 --> 01:00:15,280
"If you keep looking for me,"

859
01:00:15,780 --> 01:00:17,389
"I'll find you first."

860
01:00:35,170 --> 01:00:36,670
(Love in Trouble)

861
01:00:37,309 --> 01:00:38,840
Someone was here.

862
01:00:38,840 --> 01:00:39,840
It's you, isn't it?

863
01:00:39,840 --> 01:00:42,179
Are you worrying about me now?

864
01:00:42,809 --> 01:00:46,610
I came because you kept asking, but
I'm not sure if we can do this...

865
01:00:47,079 --> 01:00:49,449
No Ji Wook and Eun Bong Hee
were together?

866
01:00:49,449 --> 01:00:52,650
I keep feeling that I should
protect Bong Hee. It's annoying me.

867
01:00:53,050 --> 01:00:55,920
I'm going to go back
to my ex-boyfriend whom I betrayed.

868
01:00:56,059 --> 01:00:57,760
Come back to me.

869
01:00:57,860 --> 01:00:59,159
Come work with me,

870
01:00:59,659 --> 01:01:00,800
Bong Hee.
